cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a novel framework for structured prediction via adversarial learning, which involves training two separate networks, i.e., the structured prediction models and the discriminative models. The proposed method is able to handle a range of tasks, e.g., multi-label classification and image segmentation, which are commonly studied in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
